{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.94",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 94,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 94 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:1",
      "text": "O Lord, thou God of vengeance, thou God of vengeance, shine forth!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:2",
      "text": "Rise up, O judge of the earth; render to the proud their deserts!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:3",
      "text": "O Lord, how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked exult?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:4",
      "text": "They pour out their arrogant words, they boast, all the evildoers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:5",
      "text": "They crush thy people, O Lord, and afflict thy heritage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:6",
      "text": "They slay the widow and the sojourner, and murder the fatherless;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:7",
      "text": "and they say, “The Lord does not see; the God of Jacob does not perceive.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:8",
      "text": "Understand, O dullest of the people! Fools, when will you be wise?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:9",
      "text": "He who planted the ear, does he not hear? He who formed the eye, does he not see?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:10",
      "text": "He who chastens the nations, does he not chastise? He who teaches men knowledge,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:11",
      "text": "the Lord, knows the thoughts of man, that they are but a breath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:12",
      "text": "Blessed is the man whom thou dost chasten, O Lord, and whom thou dost teach out of thy law",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:13",
      "text": "to give him respite from days of trouble, until a pit is dug for the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:14",
      "text": "For the Lord will not forsake his people; he will not abandon his heritage;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:15",
      "text": "for justice will return to the righteous, and all the upright in heart will follow it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:16",
      "text": "Who rises up for me against the wicked? Who stands up for me against evildoers?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:17",
      "text": "If the Lord had not been my help, my soul would soon have dwelt in the land of silence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:18",
      "text": "When I thought, “My foot slips,” thy steadfast love, O Lord, held me up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:19",
      "text": "When the cares of my heart are many, thy consolations cheer my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:20",
      "text": "Can wicked rulers be allied with thee, who frame mischief by statute?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:21",
      "text": "They band together against the life of the righteous, and condemn the innocent to death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:22",
      "text": "But the Lord has become my stronghold, and my God the rock of my refuge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.94.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 94,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 94:23",
      "text": "He will bring back on them their iniquity and wipe them out for their wickedness; the Lord our God will wipe them out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
